@startuml session_flow
title Session Management — Login, Authenticated Request, Logout

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam sequenceArrowFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceParticipantPadding 20

actor "ATM Client" as ATM
participant "Middleware" as MW
database "middleware_db\n(session_state)" as DB
participant "Core Banking" as CB

== Phase 1 — Login ==

ATM -> MW : POST /atm/login\n{accountNumber, pin}

MW -> CB : POST /atm/login\n{accountNumber, pin}
CB --> MW : 200 OK\n{token (JWT), accountId, balance, customerName}

MW -> DB : INSERT session_state\nsession_token = random hex(32)\njwt, account_id, account_number,\nbalance, customer_name,\nlast_active = now, created_at = now
DB --> MW : OK

MW --> ATM : 200 OK\n{sessionToken, customerName, balance, ...}\n**JWT is NOT returned to ATM**

== Phase 2 — Deposit (authenticated) ==

ATM -> MW : POST /atm/deposit\nX-Session-Token: <token>\nIdempotency-Key: ...\n{amount: 500}

MW -> DB : SELECT by session_token
DB --> MW : row found, not expired

MW -> DB : UPDATE last_active = now
DB --> MW : OK

note right of MW
  Middleware reads jwt from row
  and forwards to Core Banking
end note

MW -> CB : POST /accounts/{account_id}/deposit\nAuthorization: Bearer <jwt>\n{amountDeposit: 500}
CB --> MW : 200 OK\n{transactionId, balanceAfter, ...}

MW -> DB : UPDATE balance = balanceAfter
DB --> MW : OK

MW --> ATM : 200 OK\n{status: SUCCESS, newBalance, ...}

== Phase 2b — Session continue (optional) ==

ATM -> MW : POST /atm/session/continue\nX-Session-Token: <token>

MW -> DB : UPDATE last_active = now\n(touch only — no banking call)
DB --> MW : OK

MW --> ATM : 200 OK\n{status: ok}

note right of MW
  Customer chose another transaction;
  extends the server idle window
  (SESSION_TTL_SECONDS, default 30 min)
  without deposit/withdraw.
  See Figure 11 for full UI → middleware flow.
end note

== Phase 3 — Logout ==

ATM -> MW : POST /atm/logout\nX-Session-Token: <token>

MW -> DB : DELETE session_state\nWHERE session_token = <token>
DB --> MW : OK

MW --> ATM : 200 OK\n{status: logged_out}

note right of MW #FFEEEE
  Same token cannot be reused.
  Next request → HTTP 401.
end note

@enduml
